title: Tennis Roundup: River Valley at sectional
text:
Tennis Roundup: River Valley at sectional 9:37 p.m. EDT October 1, 2015 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Division II sectional 
Taylor Hawk won two singles matches 6-1, 6-0 and 6-0, 6-0 before falling 0-6, 0-6 to top seed Marasa Madison of Columbus School for Girls Thursday in the Division II sectional tournament at Columbus Academy. Izzy Smith won her opening match 6-0, 6-0 for the Vikings. Julie Lackey lost her opening match 0-6, 0-6. In doubles, Paayal Vora/Shay Call lost 5-7, 2-6 in the second round after an opening win by forfeit and Leah Devore/Allison Edwards lost 3-6, 3-6 in their opening match. 
Division I sectional 
Both doubles teams won first-round matches for Marion Harding Thursday in the Division I sectional at Upper Arlington. Maggie Pitts/Allison Russell won 6-2, 6-0 before losing 1-6, 0-6. Sidney Street/Madison Randolph won 6-7, 6-3, 7-6 before losing in the second round. In singles, Alyssa Moodley lost 6-7, 1-6, Fallyn Stephens lost 2-6, 3-6 and Ashley Russell lost 0-6, 0-6.
